Add a splash of colour to your ensemble. This beautiful tussar muga silk stole is perfect for all. Tie-dyed with vibrant poppy colours it's absolutely marvelous. Drape it over a top and denim for a chic uptown girl look. Did you know?Tie- Dye is a technique of patterning cloth by reserving a part of the surface before dyeing. This is done by marking the fabric with patterns and blocking the penetration of the dye by tying the reserved area tightly with thread. The tied fabric is then dipped into vats of dye to create resist-dye patterns which vary in complexity of technique and design. Bandhni Lehriya and Mothra are prime examples of hand ti-dyed fabric.
